@startuml snapshot-flow
!theme plain

title Snapshot Flow

participant "ConnectorTask" as Task
participant "SnapshotSource" as Snap
participant "Neo4j DB" as Neo4j
participant "OffsetContext" as Offset
participant "Kafka" as Kafka

Task -> Snap: start snapshot

== 1. Capture streaming start point BEFORE snapshot ==

Snap -> Neo4j: CALL db.cdc.current()
Neo4j --> Snap: changeId = "ABC123..."
Snap -> Offset: store changeId as resume point

== 2. Snapshot nodes (for each captured label) ==

loop For each label in node.label.include.list
    Snap -> Neo4j: MATCH (n:Label)\nRETURN elementId(n),\n  labels(n), properties(n)
    Neo4j --> Snap: result set
    Snap -> Kafka: emit "read" (r) events\nto prefix.db.node.Label
end

== 3. Snapshot relationships (for each captured type) ==

loop For each type in relationship.type.include.list
    Snap -> Neo4j: MATCH (s)-[r:TYPE]->(e)\nRETURN elementId(r),\n  type(r), ...
    Neo4j --> Snap: result set
    Snap -> Kafka: emit "read" (r) events\nto prefix.db.relationship.TYPE
end

== 4. Snapshot complete ==

Snap -> Offset: mark snapshot completed
Snap --> Task: done, hand off to streaming

@enduml
